---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - MacParakeet" description="MacParakeet privacy policy. Your audio never leaves your Mac.">
  <header class="fixed top-0 left-0 right-0 z-50 bg-slate-950/80 backdrop-blur-md border-b border-slate-800">
    <nav class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between">
      <a href="/" class="text-xl font-bold flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="text-2xl">🦜</span>
        MacParakeet
      </a>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main class="pt-32 pb-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-invert">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="lead text-slate-400">
        Last updated: January 24, 2026
      </p>

      <h2>The Short Version</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Your audio never leaves your Mac.</strong> MacParakeet processes everything locally. We don't collect, store, or transmit any of your data.
      </p>

      <h2>What We Don't Collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Audio files</strong> - Your recordings are processed entirely on your device</li>
        <li><strong>Transcriptions</strong> - Your text output stays on your Mac</li>
        <li><strong>Usage analytics</strong> - No tracking, no telemetry</li>
        <li><strong>Personal information</strong> - No accounts, no login required</li>
        <li><strong>Device identifiers</strong> - No fingerprinting</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How MacParakeet Works</h2>
      <p>
        MacParakeet uses the Parakeet TDT model running locally on your Mac via Apple's MLX framework. When you transcribe audio:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Audio is loaded into memory on your Mac</li>
        <li>The Parakeet model processes it locally</li>
        <li>Transcription results are displayed in the app</li>
        <li>Temporary files are deleted after processing</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        At no point does audio data leave your device.
      </p>

      <h2>Network Connections</h2>
      <p>
        MacParakeet does not send your audio or transcripts to any server.
      </p>
      <p>
        The app may use the network only for setup and maintenance tasks such as:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Model downloads</strong> - downloading local STT/LLM model files (when applicable)</li>
        <li><strong>Dependency installs</strong> - installing local Python packages needed to run the STT daemon</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        These connections are for downloading software components only. Your recordings and transcripts stay on-device.
      </p>

      <h2>Data Storage</h2>
      <p>
        MacParakeet stores minimal data locally on your Mac:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Settings</strong> - Your preferences (hotkey, behavior)</li>
        <li><strong>History</strong> - Dictation and transcription history stored locally</li>
        <li><strong>Models</strong> - Downloaded AI models for local processing</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        All data is stored in standard macOS locations and can be deleted by removing the app.
      </p>

      <h2>Third Parties</h2>
      <p>
        MacParakeet does not share any data with third parties because we don't collect any data to share.
      </p>

      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        MacParakeet does not collect any personal information from anyone, including children under 13.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        If we update this privacy policy, we'll post the changes here. Since MacParakeet doesn't collect data, significant changes are unlikely.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about privacy? Email us at <a href="mailto:privacy@macparakeet.com">privacy@macparakeet.com</a>.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">
        This privacy policy is intentionally simple because MacParakeet is designed to respect your privacy by default. We believe the best privacy policy is one where there's nothing to disclose.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="py-12 px-6 border-t border-slate-800">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="text-xl">🦜</span>
        <span class="font-semibold">MacParakeet</span>
      </div>
      <div class="text-slate-500 text-sm">
        © 2026 MacParakeet. All rights reserved.
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Tailwind v4: avoid @apply in component styles (requires @reference).
     Keep these styles plain CSS to ensure `astro build` works. */
  .prose h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #fff;
  }
  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: rgb(203 213 225);
  }
  .prose ul,
  .prose ol {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    margin-left: 1.5rem;
    color: rgb(203 213 225);
  }
  .prose li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .prose a {
    color: rgb(96 165 250);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .prose a:hover {
    color: rgb(147 197 253);
  }
  .prose hr {
    margin: 2rem 0;
    border: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid rgb(30 41 59);
  }
</style>
